        <h2>Routing &amp; Switching</h2>

        <p>Dr. Lavian offers expert consulting services for routing protocols, routers, switch architecture and design, standards, and network protocols. Routing and switching are the backbone of networking. This area includes detailed knowledge in routing and switching protocols, design, operations, and troubleshooting, as well as deep knowledge in the OSI 7-layer model and its practical application.</p>

        <p>Dr. Lavian has extensive hands-on experience and has conducted extensive research in telecommunications, networking, routing &amp; switching, and cloud computing networking. He has published numerous peer-reviewed research papers and holds 38 US patents, many in the areas of routing &amp; switching, networking, computing, and telecommunications.</p>

        <p>He has the necessary research and development background to offer routing &amp; switching expert witness services. He brings a unique combination of research, academic, and industry experience in telecommunications, networking, and computer science to provide expert witness consulting services.</p>

        <p>A router is a networking device that forwards data packets between computer networks. Routers perform the traffic directing functions between networks and on the global Internet. Data sent through a router, such as a web page or email, is in the form of data packets. A router connects two or more data lines from different IP networks. When a data packet arrives at one of the lines, the router reads the network address information in the packet header to determine its final destination. Then, using information in its routing table or routing policy, it directs the packet to the next network on its journey. Routers and switches work in tandem, with switches directing traffic within a local network and routers directing traffic between different networks.</p>

