        <p>Network infrastructure comprises the hardware and software resources of an entire network that enable network connectivity, communication, operations, and management of an enterprise network. Network infrastructure provides the communication paths and services between users, processes, applications, services, and external networks and the Internet.</p>

        <p>Network infrastructure is Telecomm NET&rsquo;s primary area of expertise. This expertise encompasses a deep knowledge in routing &amp; switching, switching &amp; routing protocols, router &amp; switch hardware and software technologies, and network architecture.</p>

        <h3>Routing &amp; Switching Protocols</h3>

        <p>Routing and switching protocols manage data flow within a computer network. Routing protocols, like BGP (Border Gateway Protocol) and OSPF (Open Shortest Path First), determine the best path for data packets to travel across interconnected networks by exchanging routing information between routers. Switching protocols operate at the data link layer and include protocols such as ATM (Asynchronous Transfer Mode) and Ethernet, facilitating communication between devices within the same network by using MAC addresses. These protocols are essential for creating efficient, resilient, and scalable networks, ensuring data reaches its intended destination quickly and reliably.</p>

        <h3>Routers and Switches Hardware Technologies</h3>

        <p>Routers and switches are two networking hardware devices that forward data packets between computer networks. A switch is typically used to connect devices within a single local area network (LAN), while a router is used to connect multiple networks, such as a LAN and the Internet.</p>

        <p>Routers typically have several ports for connecting to other devices, such as computers, modems, and switches. They use routing tables to determine the best path for forwarding data packets and can perform functions such as packet filtering, Quality of Service (QoS), and network address translation (NAT). Some routers also offer features such as port aggregation, wireless connectivity, and VPN support.</p>

        <p>Overall, routers and switches are critical components of modern computer networks and are used in a wide variety of settings, including homes, small businesses, large enterprises, and service provider networks. They work together to provide reliable and efficient connectivity for devices within a network and between different networks.</p>

